    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Distancias cuadráticas par a par.\n",
        "diff = X_spec[:, None, :] - X_spec[None, :, :]\n",
        "dist2 = np.sum(diff**2, axis=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Escala del kernel.\n",
        "sigma = 0.35\n",
        "\n",
        "# Kernel Gaussiano.\n",
        "W_full = np.exp(-dist2 / (2 * sigma**2))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Eliminamos autociclos.\n",
        "np.fill_diagonal(W_full, 0.0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Grafo k-vecinos más cercanos.\n",
        "k_neighbors = 12\n",
        "W_knn = np.zeros_like(W_full)\n",
        "\n",
        "for i in range(W_full.shape[0]):\n",
        "    idx_neighbors = np.argsort(dist2[i])[1:k_neighbors + 1]\n",
        "    W_knn[i, idx_neighbors] = W_full[i, idx_neighbors]\n",
        "\n",
        "# 'Simetrizamos' la matriz para trabajar con un grafo no dirigido.\n",
        "W_spec = np.maximum(W_knn, W_knn.T)"
      ],
      "id": "facdf40b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Con la matriz de similitud construimos la matriz de grados y la matriz simétrica normalizada $\\mathbf{S}=\\mathbf{D}^{-1/2}\\mathbf{W}\\mathbf{D}^{-1/2}$:"
      ],
      "id": "7a94662c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Matriz de grados.\n",
        "degrees = W_spec.sum(axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Evitamos divisiones por cero.\n",
        "degrees = np.where(degrees == 0, 1e-12, degrees)\n",
        "\n",
        "D_inv_sqrt = np.diag(1 / np.sqrt(degrees))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Matriz normalizada tipo Ng-Jordan-Weiss.\n",
        "S_spec = D_inv_sqrt @ W_spec @ D_inv_sqrt"
      ],
      "id": "0d820b6c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Calculamos los autovectores derechos de $\\mathbf{S}$. Como $\\mathbf{S}$ es simétrica, sus autovectores derechos también coinciden con sus autovectores izquierdos. Tomaremos los dos autovectores asociados a los autovalores más grandes y los usaremos como encaje espectral:"
      ],
      "id": "83583542"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Autovalores y autovectores de S.\n",
        "eigvals_s, eigvecs_s = np.linalg.eigh(S_spec)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ordenamos de mayor a menor autovalor.\n",
        "order = np.argsort(eigvals_s)[::-1]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Tomamos los dos autovectores principales.\n",
        "U_spec = eigvecs_s[:, order[:2]]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalización por filas, como en Ng-Jordan-Weiss.\n",
        "row_norms = np.linalg.norm(U_spec, axis=1, keepdims=True)\n",
        "row_norms = np.where(row_norms == 0, 1e-12, row_norms)\n",
        "\n",
        "Y_spec = U_spec / row_norms"
      ],
      "id": "6aa610ea",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Para clusterizar el encaje, implementaremos una versión mínima del algoritmo más elemental de clustering que existe en el aprendizaje automático, denominado algoritmo de $K$-medias. No nos interesa aquí estudiarlo en detalle, sino usarlo como una herramienta simple para agrupar los puntos del encaje espectral:"
      ],
      "id": "63dbc808"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def simple_kmeans(X, k=2, n_iter=100, seed=2026):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Implementación mínima de K-means para agrupar puntos en R^d.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Inicialización aleatoria de centroides.\n",
        "    idx = rng.choice(X.shape[0], size=k, replace=False)\n",
        "    centers = X[idx].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    for _ in range(n_iter):\n",
        "        # Distancias cuadráticas a centroides.\n",
        "        distances = np.sum((X[:, None, :] - centers[None, :, :])**2, axis=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Asignación al centroide más cercano.\n",
        "        labels = np.argmin(distances, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Actualización de centroides.\n",
        "        new_centers = centers.copy()\n",
        "        for j in range(k):\n",
        "            if np.any(labels == j):\n",
        "                new_centers[j] = X[labels == j].mean(axis=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Criterio simple de detención.\n",
        "        if np.allclose(new_centers, centers):\n",
        "            break\n",
        "\n",
        "        centers = new_centers\n",
        "\n",
        "    return labels, centers"
      ],
      "id": "6710d12e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Clustering sobre el encaje espectral.\n",
        "labels_spec, centers_spec = simple_kmeans(Y_spec, k=2, n_iter=100, seed=42)"
      ],
      "id": "dd83cec1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
